{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-11135/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-11135"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:11:35"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["overhead"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Mushroom is ground in mortar and pestle"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-11135","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-11135"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1/1756f120-a339-4de9-a321-568a67e6d5c3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:02:55.291Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As in <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW171808818 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-04714.html\"><u>the scene</u></a> when Alma forages for the mushrooms, the camera focuses on her hands as she now grates and grinds them into a powder. These moments echo and contrast with the many shots of Reynolds sewing and his seamstresses at work in the atelier. Alma’s “art” takes the form of cooking—an activity that connects her to the maternal role that Reynolds seeks to place her in and that is subverted by how she uses the mushrooms to poison her lover.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11135/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:398.3122362869198,172.06751054852327,1479.831223628692,852.6582278481011"}}}]}]}]}